Better Call Saul: A Brief Introduction

Better Call Saul is an American television drama series created by Vince Gilligan and Peter Gould. It is a prequel to the critically acclaimed series Breaking Bad and follows the story of Jimmy McGill, a small-time lawyer slowly transforming into the morally flexible Saul Goodman.

Premiering in 2015 on AMC, the show ran for 6 seasons and received critical praise for its writing, acting, and cinematography.

## Key Observations

  • The first episode hat far the highest viewership at 6.88 million, probably because of the high interest of viewers after Breaking Bad, as Better Call Saul is a spin off of it.
  • As the show went on, season on season, the viewership steadily declined, reaching an average of 1.27 million in season 6.
  • Within season the views were fluctuating less than +/-0.5 million, except for Season 1 where Episode 2 dropped by 3.46 million from the shows premiere.
